# Loop Budget

> The loop's wallet. Defines per-run token cap, per-topic iteration cap, and total cumulative cap.
> Over budget = loop halts and asks the user — does NOT silently continue burning tokens.

---

## Global rules

**No daily run-count limit.** Run as many loops per day as you want.

Caps live on the **per-topic** dimension, not per-day. A single topic's v1 / v2 / v3 / etc. all count as one loop chain. Caps apply to the chain.

> Definition of "iteration" (set by user): one iteration = one full critic-routing cycle where the foreman tries to converge the draft.

---

## Per-topic iteration caps

| Dimension | Cap | Behavior |
|---|---|---|
| **Same-topic iteration count** | **6** | After 6 unconverged iterations → halt, ask user: "this topic has iterated 6 times, should we roll back to outline?" |
| **Same-topic cumulative tokens** | **2M** | Cumulative burn hits 2M → same halt + ask |
| **Whichever cap hits first** | — | Either trigger halts the chain |

**Why 6 and not unlimited**: 6 rounds without convergence usually means the upstream outline has structural issues. Continuing to iterate is just rearranging deck chairs. This cap isn't a limit on you — it's a signal that the cost is at the wrong layer.

**Manual override**: say "continue past the cap" / "override and run N more" in the conversation. The foreman will continue and mark `override_iteration_cap: true` in STATE.md.

---

## Per-loop budget

| Dimension | Cap | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| **Per-loop token cap** | **350k** | Based on measured production loops + 30% buffer for critic round 3 or genuine ESCALATE |
| **Per-loop subagent cap** | **6** | 2 cross-review + 1 critic round 1 + 1 critic round 2 + 1 reserve + 1 emergency spawn slot |

### Expected token distribution across 6 same-topic iterations (reference, not enforced)

```
Iterations 1-2: full dual-version + cross-review + critic 2 rounds ≈ 250-300k each
Iterations 3-4: incremental rerun (inherit v1+v2, only refine body + 1 critic round) ≈ 150-200k each
Iterations 5-6: micro-edit (1-2 paragraphs + 1 critic round) ≈ 80-120k each

6-iteration total estimate ≈ 1100k → 80% buffer = 2M cumulative cap
```

If iterations 1-2 produce a winner, later token budget is unused — that's fine, save it for the next topic.

